  abstract = {Optimized kernel for the experimental opensees finite element analysis package. API Improvements In addition to substantial performance gains over upstream, the following improvements have been made to the API: Modeling new section argument added to fiber, patch and layer commands. Eliminates need for precarious dependence on global state from Python. new pattern argument added to load command; eliminates need for precarious dependence on global state from Python. new Model class eliminates need for precarious dependence on global state from Python. Removed hard-coded limit on fibers; currently upstream will produce undefined behavior is too many fibers are used. Interpreter new printA features: does not require FullGen solver; now all one needs to do is call model.getTangent(). This is possible due to the new consolidated memory ownership model. new -m, -c, -k options allow custom linear combinations of \$\textbackslash mathbf\{M\}\$, \$\textbackslash mathbf\{C\}\$ and \$\textbackslash mathbf\{K\}\$: C = model.getTangent(c=1.0) or in Tcl: printA -c 1.0 the fiber section parser has been completely reimplemented to follow a reasonable programming paradigm. improved print command new -registry option. more reliable JSON printing includes MP\_Constraint information new -det option for static integrators: ArcLength, ... fix changing reference load in static integrators new -det capability for solvers: FullGenLapack, Umfpack, BandGenLapack Verbosity control; use OPENSEESRT\_VERBOSITY new export command in Python and Tcl, when run through Python new getTangent() method for Model class in Python new invoke Tcl command and Python constructs Tcl Only new progress command in Tcl new = command, fixes vexing operator precedence in expr},
